<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-12-07T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-12-07T14:00:00-05:00" n="114" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d114">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/2600: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Minister in Bolivia (<persName type="to">Feely</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-12-07T14:00:00-05:00">December 7, 1932—2 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>55. Your 132, December 6, 11 p.m. Department hopes you will continue
                                discreetly to keep this matter before Bolivian authorities and
                                endeavor to have them accept proposal contained in Department’s No.
                                52 as modified by its No. 53. Please keep Department informed by
                                cable.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>